article.headline: Penn State 56, Hartford 55
article.story: STATE COLLEGE, Pa. (AP) -- Geary Claxton had 16 points and 10 rebounds, and Penn State held off a strong second-half rally by Hartford for a 56-55 victory on Wednesday night. Claxton, who broke the pinkie on his right hand during the preseason and missed the team's first four games, led the Nittany Lions (6-2) in scoring for the first time this season. Robert Taylor scored 12 points to lead the Hawks (3-5), who had their three-game winning streak halted. Penn State led by a point when a desperation heave by Hartford's Joe Zeglinski missed the rim. The Nittany Lions' Milos Bogetic wrestled the rebound away from Michale Turner as time expired to seal the win. Penn State led 56-55 with 1:07 left when the Zeglinski, a freshman, missed two free throws that would have put Hartford ahead. Penn State stretched a four-point halftime lead to 11 in the second half before the Hawks rallied. Zeglinski's 3-pointer capped a 12-2 run with just over five minutes remaining to make it a 51-50. Danny Morrissey put the Lions ahead for good with a fast-break lay-up after breaking the Hawks full-court press Penn State's Jamelle Cornley left the game with just over five minutes remaining after rolling his ankle. He did not return.
